update.description:
When running ``` gazebo actor.world``` prints errors ```Error [Element.hh:322] Unable to find value for key[self_collide]```

This does not happen with gazebo5 but happens in the latest ones, possibly due to changes in Link.cc.
The errors could be fixed by adding the "self_collide" element to the Actor links.

This commit gets rid of most of the error messages, but not all.
To get rid of all the error messages, some modification on actor.sdf (from sdformat) might be required.  
(Maybe there should be a "self_collide" element in actor.sdf, so that we can add the element before passing ```_sdf``` to ```Model::Load```?)

content.raw:
The remaining errors seem to do with the actor itself (the ones fixed in the commit are the errors from the links).  The error from the actor could disappear by adding ```_sdf->GetElement("self_collide")->Set(false)```, which I commented out in the commit.

The reason I commented this out, is because in order for this to work, there has to be a "self_collide" element defined in the actor.sdf. (Otherwise, the GetElement will crash gazebo)

By the way, I've tested the *"self_collide" adding to actor.sdf* in my local environment. The remaining errors did disappear when I tried this.
content.html:
The remaining errors seem to do with the actor itself (the ones fixed in the commit are the errors from the links). The error from the actor could disappear by adding _sdf->GetElement("self_collide")->Set(false), which I commented out in the commit.

The reason I commented this out, is because in order for this to work, there has to be a "self_collide" element defined in the actor.sdf. (Otherwise, the GetElement will crash gazebo)

By the way, I've tested the "self_collide" adding to actor.sdf in my local environment. The remaining errors did disappear when I tried this.
